hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'm a housewife now foods coq10 100mg softgels Washington, D.C. used to be a place where you didn't have to worry so much about security. You could go into almost any public building without even so much as a metal detector screening you first. The district also banned handguns, which, it's true, did not stop gun violence. Since D.C. is bordered by two states, including one (Virginia) where gun laws are quite lax, it wasn't too difficult to acquire a firearm and bring it over the city line. But since the Supreme Court decided the sweeping gun ban was unconstitutional, there's more of a free-for-all attitude with guns. What galls Washingtonians more is that it wasn't locals who wanted the gun ban lifted. It was people who don't even live here.
